cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Governance, Risk, and Compliance Documentation Library"
abstract: >-
  A CC BY-SA 4.0-licensed reference set for building an
  organization-neutral governance, risk, compliance, security, privacy,
  resilience, supplier, and artificial-intelligence governance
  programme. Includes ~300 documents across 11 domains plus
  jurisdiction-specific privacy annexes and sector-specific compliance
  sub-directories. Also ships the dev-security/claude-rules/ pack, a
  Claude Code rules-and-skills set distilled from the disciplines this
  library required to maintain itself, usable as a standalone Claude
  Code baseline on any project regardless of whether it has a GRC
  corpus.
message: >-
  If you redistribute this library or derivative works, the CC BY-SA 4.0
  licence requires you to attribute the library and to release your
  derivative under CC BY-SA 4.0 as well. This CITATION file provides
  the canonical citation metadata for attribution purposes. Adopters
  using only the dev-security/claude-rules/ pack should still cite
  the parent library, since the pack is a derivative artefact of the
  library's maintenance experience and ships under the same licence.
